trans-unit.source: Over time, an application will allocate large portions of memory, write data to that memory, and subsequently free some portions of it once it has finished using some of the data. This can result in "free" memory being located in non-contiguous chunks, which cannot be returned to the operating system for other applications to use. It also has an impact on the caching and access characteristics of the application, as the "living" data may be spread across many different pages of physical memory. This in turn could force the operating system to swap, which can cause filesystem I/O - which is, comparatively speaking, an extremely slow operation.

Painters are the types that visualize logical particles. For each logical particle in the groups assigned to it, which are within its bounds (or outside, if you do not set the clip property on the type) it will be visualized in a manner dependent on the type of ParticlePainter. The base type of ParticlePainter does not draw anything. ImageParticle renders an image at the particle location. CustomParticle allows you to write your own shaders to render the particles, passing in the logical particle state as vertex data. ItemParticle allows you to visualize logical particles using arbitrary QML delegates. ModelParticle is similar, but coordinates model data amongst the delegates in a similar manner to the view classes.

ImageParticle 은 입자 위치에서 이미지를 렌더링합니다. CustomParticle을 사용하면 논리 파티클 상태를 정점 데이터로 전달하여 파티클을 렌더링하기 위해 자체 셰이더를 작성할 수 있습니다. 품목 입자 사용하면 임의의 QML 델리게이트를 사용하여 논리 입자를 시각화 할 수 있습니다. trans-unit.source: Paths specified by the QML2_IMPORT_PATH environment variable

Paths to files and directories within a directory can be constructed using filePath() and absoluteFilePath(). The filePath() function returns a path to the specified file or directory relative to the path of the QDir object; absoluteFilePath() returns an absolute path to the specified file or directory. Neither of these functions checks for the existence of files or directory; they only construct paths.
trans-unit.target: 디렉토리 내의 파일 및 디렉토리에 대한 경로는 filePath () 및 absoluteFilePath ()를 사용하여 구성 할 수 있습니다 . 적인 filePath () 함수는 경로에 지정된 파일이나 디렉토리의 상대 경로를 반환 QDir의 객체를; absoluteFilePath ()는 지정된 파일 또는 디렉토리의 절대 경로를 반환합니다. 이 기능들 중 어느 것도 파일이나 디렉토리의 존재를 점검하지 않습니다. 그들은 단지 경로를 구성합니다.
